



Sir
Richmond May 8th 1781



The British Army [&c. to the words with these arms in their hands]1 to Richmond or Prince Edward Courthouse as shall be most convenient [&c.]1 And whenever it is over they shall be discharged except the number called for by my letter of the 5th inst who will be retained to perform a full Tour.
Cavalry in a due proportion [&c. to the end.]1 I am &c.,

Tho Jefferson

